# ============================================================
# Keystatic CMS — GitHub Storage + Shared Password Gate
# ============================================================
# In production, Keystatic commits blog posts directly to the GitHub repo.
# Access to /keystatic is protected by a shared password so the marketing
# team doesn't need to be added as repo collaborators — they just need a
# GitHub account to complete the OAuth step after entering the password.
#
# Setup (one-time):
#   1. Create a GitHub OAuth App at https://github.com/settings/applications/new
#        Application name:       Mama Fern CMS
#        Homepage URL:           https://mamafern.com
#        Authorization callback: https://mamafern.com/api/keystatic/github/oauth/callback
#   2. Click "Register application" → "Generate a new client secret"
#   3. Paste the client ID and secret below
#   4. Generate KEYSTATIC_SECRET:  openssl rand -hex 32
#   5. Choose a KEYSTATIC_PASSWORD for your team (you pick it, then share it)
#   6. Add all four vars to Hostinger hPanel → Websites → Manage → Environment Variables
#
# Workflow for marketing team:
#   1. Go to https://mamafern.com/keystatic
#   2. Enter the shared KEYSTATIC_PASSWORD (30-day cookie — only once per month)
#   3. Sign in with GitHub (one-time per browser via the OAuth App)
#   4. Create/edit posts → Keystatic auto-commits MDX files to GitHub
#   5. On Hostinger, run: git pull → post appears immediately (no rebuild needed)
KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
KEYSTATIC_SECRET=
KEYSTATIC_PASSWORD=
NEXT_PUBLIC_KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_APP_SLUG=

# ============================================================
# Hosting — Hostinger Node.js
# ============================================================
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=production
